-- Yankees Sign Pitcher Chien-Ming Wang to Minor-League Contract
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-03-23T16:17:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-23/yankees-sign-pitcher-chien-ming-wang-to-minor-league-contract.html
The  New York  Yankees signed right-
handed pitcher Chien-Ming Wang to a one-year minor league
contract, the Major League Baseball team said in a statement.  Wang, 32, pitched for the Yankees from 2005-2009, posting a
55-26 record with a 4.16 earned run average in 109 games, with
104 starts. He spent the past three years with the Washington
Nationals, sitting out in 2010 while recovering from shoulder
surgery, and is 61-32 with a 4.26 ERA over his seven major-
league seasons.  Wang is Taiwanese.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  